# MCP Tools: githubmcp (Inspect)

ALWAYS include `arguments` in CallMcpTool calls. NEVER send empty `{}`.

Zero-argument tools are intentionally skipped here: `get_rate_limit`.

### get_repo_info
Get metadata and overview information about a repository.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "get_repo_info", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World" } })

### get_repo_structure
Get the file/folder tree structure of a repository.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| ref | string\|null | No | null | Branch, tag, or SHA |
| max_depth | integer\|null | No | null | Maximum depth of tree |
| path_filter | string\|null | No | null | Glob pattern to filter paths |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "get_repo_structure", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", max_depth: 2 } })

