### search_code
Search for text or regex patterns across files.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| query | string | Yes | - | Search string or regex pattern |
| is_regexp | boolean | No | false | Treat query as Python regex |
| include_pattern | string\|null | No | null | Glob pattern for files |
| ref | string\|null | No | null | Branch, tag, or SHA |
| max_results | integer | No | 50 | Maximum matching lines |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "search_code", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", query: "function main" } })

### find_files
Search for files matching a glob pattern.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| owner | string | Yes | - | Repository owner |
| repo | string | Yes | - | Repository name |
| pattern | string | Yes | - | Glob pattern |
| ref | string\|null | No | null | Branch, tag, or SHA |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "githubmcp", toolName: "find_files", arguments: { owner: "octocat", repo: "Hello-World", pattern: "**/*.js" } })

